--------------------------------------------------------------------------
SCOPE — READ THIS FIRST
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

This licence covers CHARACTER CONTENT ONLY: the authored data that defines a
Synthesus character, including but not limited to bio, personality, knowledge
and pattern files, character archives (`.sxc`), and identity chains.

This licence does NOT cover the Synthesus engine or runtime, which is licensed
separately under the GNU Affero General Public License v3 (see
`apps/synthesus/LICENSE`). The two are distinct works, deliberately separated:
the engine is free software; the characters are proprietary content that runs
on it.

Nothing in this licence adds restrictions to AGPL-licensed code, and nothing in
the AGPL grants rights over the content covered here. If you modify or
redistribute the engine, your AGPL rights and obligations are unaffected.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
GRANT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a SUBSCRIPTION licence. Rights granted here exist for as long as your
subscription is active, and not afterwards.

For the term of an active subscription covering the character in question, you
are granted a non-exclusive, non-transferable licence to:

  (a) install and run the character content on devices you own or control;
  (b) interact with it for personal or internal business purposes;
  (c) accumulate identity-chain history from your own use of it.

Coverage is determined by a signed entitlement issued to your account, which
names the plan and the characters it includes. Your device verifies that
entitlement locally; see "WHAT LEAVES YOUR MACHINE" below.

GRACE. An entitlement is short-lived and renews automatically while your
subscription is active. If your device cannot reach the renewal service — you
are travelling, offline, or a payment needs attention — the character continues
to run throughout a grace period after the entitlement expires. The product is
not designed to stop working the moment it cannot phone home.

WHEN A SUBSCRIPTION ENDS. The character stops running. Nothing else changes:
see "YOUR DATA IS YOURS" below. Resubscribing restores the character, and it
resumes from the identity chain already on your machine.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
RESTRICTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

You may not, without prior written permission:

  1. redistribute, resell, sublicense, lease, rent, or publish the character
     content, in original or modified form;
  2. use the character content to train, fine-tune, distil, or otherwise derive
     a model, character, or dataset intended to reproduce or substitute for it;
  3. remove, alter, or obscure the archive manifest, its digests, licence
     metadata, or any attribution;
  4. represent a modified character as genuine, or as issued or endorsed by the
     copyright holder.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS AND IS NOT CLAIMED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Stated plainly, because overclaiming helps nobody:

  * Entitlement checking is NOT copy protection. You control your hardware and
    can bypass the check. Its purpose is to make the legitimate path automatic
    for people who want the product to work, not to defeat someone who owns the
    computer. It must not be sold as DRM.

  * The archive format provides INTEGRITY, not authenticity. A digest proves an
    archive is intact and self-consistent. It does not prove who produced it.
    Until archives are signed, an archive must not be described as "verified
    genuine" on the strength of its digest alone.

  * Character content is delivered to, and runs on, hardware you control. No
    technical measure prevents you from reading it. The protection here is
    legal, not technical, and is stated as such.

  * An identity chain records history that is internally consistent and rooted
    in a specific character archive. It is tamper-evident. It does not prove
    who ran it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
YOUR DATA IS YOURS — INCLUDING AFTER YOU CANCEL
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Identity-chain entries, conversation history and any files produced by your use
are YOUR data. The copyright holder claims no ownership of them, requires no
access to them, and this licence does not permit collecting them.

A subscription buys the right to RUN a character. It never buys the right to
withhold what your own machine recorded. Specifically, when a subscription
lapses:

  * your identity chain remains readable and exportable;
  * your conversation history remains readable;
  * files on your machine remain yours and readable;
  * only the character's ability to run stops.

Nothing in this licence permits deleting, encrypting, disabling access to, or
holding to ransom data on your own hardware.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHAT LEAVES YOUR MACHINE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Stated exactly, because the product's central claim depends on it.

Your prompts, conversations, files, identity chain and results are processed on
your own devices and are NOT sent to the copyright holder.

To renew a subscription entitlement, your device contacts the renewal service.
That request discloses that a subscription is in use. It carries no prompts, no
conversation content, no file contents, no identity-chain data, and no usage
statistics. The entitlement returned contains only: your account and
subscription identifiers, the plan name, the characters covered, its validity
dates, and a signature.

This is therefore not "nothing leaves your machine". It is "nothing about your
work leaves your machine", and the difference is stated rather than glossed.

